referenceFunction.name: copper, at regional storage
referenceFunction.includedProcesses: Transport of primary metal to Europe from the countries importing to Europe is included, as the import of concentrate, which is processed in RER. As import pattern the situation of Germany in 1994 was chosen.
referenceFunction.generalComment: The module characterises the copper used in Germany 1994 reflecting its origin and the fraction of secondary metal. It is designed for the use of the metal various technical applications such as alloys and construction material.

geography.text: In this module the consumption pattern of Germany is used as proxy for the situation in RER.

technology.text: This consumption mix represents the technology used of the countries importing to Germany in 1994 and differentiates between pyrolytical processes, hydrolytical processes and secondary copper.

source.additionalAuthors: Blaser S., Classen M., Jungbluth N.
source.title: Life Cycle Inventories of Metals
